  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting when you choose this tradition at 3rd level, your mystical touch can mend wounds as easily as it can inflict them. At the start of your turn, you can spend 1 ki point to focus it into your hands gaining the following benefits:</p><ul><li><strong>Hand of Harm</strong>. When you hit a creature with an unarmed strike, you can deal bonus extra necrotic or poison damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die + your Wisdom modifier. You only deal this bonus damage once per turn.</li><li><strong>Hand of Healing</strong>. As an action, you can touch a creature and restore a number of hit points equal to a roll of your Martial Arts die + your Wisdom modifier.</li><li>When you use your Flurry of Blows, you can replace one of the unarmed strikes with a <strong>Hand of Healing</strong>.</li></ul>",
